+# gpt_image_edit
+
+## What it does
+
+Edits an image using OpenAI's image generation via the Responses API (`gpt-image-1` under the hood). Each record on the input lane is a self-contained JSON document carrying the frame, the references and the prompt — no per-pipeline configuration of refs is needed.
+
+## Lanes
+
+| Input  | Output  |
+| ------ | ------- |
+| `text` | `image` |
+
+## Per-record JSON
+
+```json
+{
+  "frame_b64": "<base64 PNG>",
+  "ref_b64s": ["<base64 PNG>", "<base64 PNG>"],
+  "prompt": "Replace the person with the reference character...",
+  "quality": "low",          // optional, overrides node default
+  "size": "1024x1024"        // optional, overrides node default
+}
+```
+
+- `frame_b64` (required): base64-encoded image to edit.
+- `ref_b64s` (required): 1–4 base64-encoded reference images.
+- `prompt` (required): editing instructions.
+- `quality`, `size`: optional per-record overrides.
+
+The node uploads `frame_b64` and every entry of `ref_b64s` to the OpenAI Files API (`purpose=vision`) on every record, then calls the Responses API `image_generation` tool with the resulting file_ids.
+
+## Configuration
+
+| Field        | Required | Description                                  |
+| ------------ | -------- | -------------------------------------------- |
+| `apikey`     | yes      | OpenAI API key.                              |
+| `model`      | no       | Responses model (default `gpt-5.5`).         |
+| `quality`    | no       | Default rendering quality (record overrides).|
+| `size`       | no       | Default output resolution (record overrides).|
+| `moderation` | no       | `auto` (default) or `low`.                   |
+
+## Example pipeline
+
+```text
+webhook → text → gpt_image_edit → image → response_image
+```
+
+## Upstream docs
+
+- https://developers.openai.com/api/docs/guides/image-generation
+- https://developers.openai.com/api/docs/api-reference/files
