@@ -0,0 +1,26 @@
+# openai_files_upload
+
+## What it does
+
+Uploads each incoming image to the OpenAI Files API and emits the resulting `file_id` as text. Use this when downstream nodes need an OpenAI file reference instead of raw image bytes (e.g. the Responses API `image_generation` tool, vision inputs, batch jobs).
+
+## Lanes
+
+| Input   | Output |
+| ------- | ------ |
+| `image` | `text` |
+
+## Configuration
+
+| Field     | Required | Description                                     |
+| --------- | -------- | ----------------------------------------------- |
+| `apikey`  | yes      | OpenAI API key.                                 |
+| `purpose` | no       | Files API purpose (default `vision`).           |
+
+## Output
+
+A single text line per image: the OpenAI file_id (e.g. `file-Xz4JE...`).
+
+## Upstream docs
+
+- https://developers.openai.com/api/docs/api-reference/files
